<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,1171,1581]" lastBlockId="5.[113,1089,223,471]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">
This species was transferred from the nominotypical subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Westwood, 1834" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1834" box="[833,1127,1269,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[833,947,1269,1293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Microvelia</emphasis>
Westwood, 1834
</taxonomicName>
to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1913" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1913" box="[327,576,1301,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Picaultia">
<emphasis box="[327,424,1301,1325]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Picaultia</emphasis>
Distant, 1913
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="ANDERSEN N. M. &amp; WEIR T. A." box="[619,896,1301,1325]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="261 - 348" refId="ref7873" refString="ANDERSEN N. M. &amp; WEIR T. A. 2003: The genus Microvelia Westwood in Australia (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae). Invertebrate Systematics 17: 261 - 348." type="journal article" year="2003">ANDERSEN &amp; WEIR (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. It is a poorly known species described from the southern Turkish provinces of Adana (locality Suluhan near Kozan) and Gaziantep (localities Kilis and Afrin river near Musabeyli) by 
<bibRefCitation author="HOBERLANDT L." box="[905,1123,1364,1389]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref8635" refString="HOBERLANDT L. 1952: Results of the Zoological Scientific Expedition of the National Museum of Prague to Turkey. 2. Hemiptera - Heteroptera 1. The aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera of Turkey. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 26 (352) (1948): 1 - 74 + 9 pls." type="book chapter" year="1952">HOBERLANDT (1952)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="ANDERSEN N. M." box="[151,328,1396,1421]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="77 - 114" refId="ref7802" refString="ANDERSEN N. M. 1995: Infraorder Gerromorpha Popov, 1971 - semiaquatic bugs. Pp. 77 - 114. In: AUKEMA B. &amp; RIEGER Ch. (eds.): Catalogue of the Heteroptera of the Palaearctic Region. Vol. 1. Enicocephalomorpha, Dipsocoromorpha, Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha and Leptopodomorpha. The Netherlands Entomological Society, Amsterdam, xxvi + 222 pp." type="book chapter" year="1995">ANDERSEN (1995)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="ANDERSEN N. M. &amp; WEIR T. A." box="[375,636,1397,1421]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="261 - 348" refId="ref7873" refString="ANDERSEN N. M. &amp; WEIR T. A. 2003: The genus Microvelia Westwood in Australia (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae). Invertebrate Systematics 17: 261 - 348." type="journal article" year="2003">ANDERSEN &amp; WEIR (2003)</bibRefCitation>
listed it also from 
<collectingCountry box="[823,961,1397,1421]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="BROWN E. S." box="[968,1126,1396,1421]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="432 - 433" refId="ref8076" refString="BROWN E. S. 1953 a: Additional records of aquatic Hemiptera from Arabia. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (12) 6: 432 - 433." type="journal article" year="1953">BROWN (1953a)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned three females from Hejaz and Northern ’ 
<collectingRegion box="[708,758,1429,1453]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="'Asir" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Asir</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[774,917,1429,1453]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
) but found ‘impossible to state whether they belong to the typical form or 
<taxonomicName authority="Brown" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="1953" box="[746,976,1461,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hozari" subSpecies="macani">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[820,898,1461,1484]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">macani</emphasis>
Brown
</taxonomicName>
(in press)’. In the subsequent paper, 
<bibRefCitation author="BROWN E. S." box="[394,560,1492,1517]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="579 - 600" refId="ref8107" refString="BROWN E. S. 1953 b: Notes on aquatic Heteroptera from Syria and Iraq. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (12) 6: 579 - 600." type="journal article" year="1953">BROWN (1953b)</bibRefCitation>
described the subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="Brown, 1953" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hozari" subSpecies="macani">
<emphasis box="[845,867,1493,1516]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[884,1038,1493,1517]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">hozari macani</emphasis>
Brown, 1953
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[266,360,1525,1549]" country="Iraq" name="Baghdad" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Baghdad</collectingRegion>
and attributed the Saudi Arabian specimens to the nominotypical subspecies. However, the species was not included in the review of Saudi Arabian 
<taxonomicName box="[968,1093,1557,1580]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heteroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Heteroptera</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAVUORI R. E." box="[113,312,223,247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="8" pagination="31 - 97" refId="ref9498" refString="LINNAVUORI R. E. 1986: Heteroptera of Saudi Arabia. Fauna of Saudi Arabia 8: 31 - 97." type="journal article" year="1986">LINNAVUORI (1986)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="CARL M." box="[321,451,223,247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="8" pagination="12 - 20" refId="ref8195" refString="CARL M. 1989: Aquatische Insekten aus dem Irak: Ihre Verbreitung und Lebensraume (Ephemeroptera, Odonata, Heteroptera, Coleoptera, Diptera). Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen 38: 12 - 20." type="journal article" year="1989">CARL (1989)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoberlandt" authorityYear="1952" box="[555,658,223,247]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hozari">
<emphasis box="[555,658,223,247]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">M. hozari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from irrigation ditches in Baiji (environs of Tikrīt) in 
<collectingCountry box="[255,301,256,279]" name="Iraq" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">Iraq</collectingCountry>
; these specimens might be misidentified 
<emphasis box="[761,783,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">M</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[809,825,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[851,929,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">macani</emphasis>
Brown, 1953. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoberlandt" authorityYear="1952" box="[113,302,287,311]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hozari">
<emphasis box="[113,302,287,311]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">Microvelia hozari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was listed from 
<collectingCountry box="[472,515,288,311]" name="Iraq" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">Iraq</collectingCountry>
neither by 
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAVUORI R. E." box="[631,824,287,311]" pageId="5" pageNumber="8" pagination="87 - 95" refId="ref9558" refString="LINNAVUORI R. E. 1994: Hemiptera of Iraq. IV. Heteroptera, the aquatic and subaquatic families, Saldidae and Leptopodidae. Entomologica Fennica 5: 87 - 95." type="journal article" year="1994">LINNAVUORI (1994)</bibRefCitation>
nor by 
<bibRefCitation author="ANDERSEN N. M." box="[902,1085,287,312]" pageId="5" pageNumber="8" pagination="77 - 114" refId="ref7802" refString="ANDERSEN N. M. 1995: Infraorder Gerromorpha Popov, 1971 - semiaquatic bugs. Pp. 77 - 114. In: AUKEMA B. &amp; RIEGER Ch. (eds.): Catalogue of the Heteroptera of the Palaearctic Region. Vol. 1. Enicocephalomorpha, Dipsocoromorpha, Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha and Leptopodomorpha. The Netherlands Entomological Society, Amsterdam, xxvi + 222 pp." type="book chapter" year="1995">ANDERSEN (1995)</bibRefCitation>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="HOBERLANDT L." box="[258,468,319,343]" pageId="5" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref8635" refString="HOBERLANDT L. 1952: Results of the Zoological Scientific Expedition of the National Museum of Prague to Turkey. 2. Hemiptera - Heteroptera 1. The aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera of Turkey. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 26 (352) (1948): 1 - 74 + 9 pls." type="book chapter" year="1952">HOBERLANDT (1952)</bibRefCitation>
, the Turkish specimens were collected ‘on small water surfaces (at the Afrin river, unfar the course proper of the river in tiny puddles formed by the hoofs of cattle) exposed to constant insolation, without special vegetation’. Our specimen was found in fields near Erdemli in a small puddle fed by a leaking irrigation pipe. Additional record from 
<collectingCountry box="[246,322,447,471]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and the first one from the İçel province.
</paragraph>
